ngs not at all to sensual pleasures He is the one I call a brahminWith burden lowered and detached He is the one I call a brahminAnd has attained the goal supreme He is the one I call a brahminWho wanders without home or wish He is the one I call a brahminWho does not kill or have them killed He is the one I call a brahminWho does not cling among those who cling He is the one I call a brahminLike mustard seed on the point of an awl He is the one I call a brahminWhich does not damage anyone He is the one I call a brahminSmall or big or fair or foul He is the one I call a brahminWho lives unyearning and detached He is the one I call a brahminThrough having reached the Deathless Sphere He is the one I call a brahminIs sorrowless stainless and pure He is the one I call a brahminDelight and being have been destroyed He is the one I call a brahminWho has crossed to the further shore And meditates within the jhanasIs unperturbed and unperplexed Attained Nibbana through no clinging He is the one I call a brahminWith sense desires and being destroyed He is the one I call a brahminWith craving and being both destroyed He is the one I call a brahminDetached from all bonds everywhere He is the one I call a brahminThe hero who has transcended the whole world He is the one I call a brahminUnclutching he sublime awake He is the one I call a brahminAn arahant with taints destroyed He is the one I call a brahminWho is unimpeded and clings no more He is the one I call a brahminUnperturbed cleansed awakened He is the one I call a brahminWho has reached the destruction of birth He is the one I call a brahminOriginating in conventions They are assigned here and thereNot knowing they declare to us One is a brahmin by birthAnd men are merchants by their acts And by their acts are servants tooAnd men are chaplains by their acts And by their acts are rulers tooSeers of dependent origination Skilled in action and its resultsAction makes the world go round Action makes this generation turnAsc